      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "Outgoing longwave radiation during the night will be severely restricted. For this reason the snowpack will only just freeze. Sunshine and high temperatures will give rise as the day progresses to increasing and thorough wetting of the snowpack below approximately 2800 m. The high humditiy will give rise in the afternoon to a loss of strength within the snowpack also on steep shady slopes. <br/> West, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2200 m: Towards its base, the snowpack consists of faceted crystals."
      },
